It was a night of glitz, glamour and drama as celebrities and influencers came into the Premiere of the most anticipated Nollywood movie of the year “Love Is War” which held on at the weekend at Filmhouse Cinemas, Lekki. <img class="size-full wp-image-1259893 aligncenter" src="https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/0b5035ec-3901-4859-84bb-1f66039cc309.jpg?resize=640%2C960&#038;ssl=1" alt="Night of Glitz" width="640" height="960" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/0b5035ec-3901-4859-84bb-1f66039cc309.jpg?w=679&amp;ssl=1 679w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/0b5035ec-3901-4859-84bb-1f66039cc309.jpg?resize=200%2C300&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/0b5035ec-3901-4859-84bb-1f66039cc309.jpg?resize=39%2C58&amp;ssl=1 39w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/0b5035ec-3901-4859-84bb-1f66039cc309.jpg?resize=129%2C194&amp;ssl=1 129w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/0b5035ec-3901-4859-84bb-1f66039cc309.jpg?resize=87%2C130&amp;ssl=1 87w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/0b5035ec-3901-4859-84bb-1f66039cc309.jpg?resize=560%2C840&amp;ssl=1 560w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> The movie, directed by Omoni Oboli was written by Chinaza Onuzo and produced by Inkblot Productions in collaboration with Dioni Visions Entertainment. The political-themed event presented a night of power and wealth, as celebrities and other guests showed up to support their candidate. The gubernatorial candidate, Omoni Oboli dressed up in a red dress and ready for the elections while Richard Mofe Damijo in a brown agbada and a navy blue Fila and Damilare Kuku looking as beautiful as ever ready to give all her support to her parents. Supporters of Mr and Mrs Phillips came all out to support their candidates and did all their best to make their candidates look good for the elections. It was a night filled with drama as the supporters of the two candidates rallied for their next governor. The INEC chairman, Ayo Makun, came out to tell everyone the results were inconclusive, as reruns will be held on the 27th of September when the film opens in cinemas. Guests at the grand premiere included Ayo Makun, Funke Akindele, Toke Makinwa, Sharon Ooja, Alex Ekubo, Inidima Okojie, Mercy Aigbe, Tope Oshin, Sophie Alakija all came to give their support to the gubernatorial candidates. Love is War is a story about a married couple Mr Phillips (Mofe Damijo) and Mrs Phillips (Omoni Oboli) who go head to head for a governorship position. The movie is set for nationwide release on the 27th of September. Vanguard After a successful two weeks in cinemas ‘Being Mrs Elliott’ the highly anticipated movie from Nollywood actress, director and producer, Omoni Oboli has lived up to expectations in the cinema with high box office sales September 18, 2014 In "Entertainment" Nollywood actress cum producer, Omoni Oboli got what she did not bargain for, last Friday night, when the premiere of her much-talked about movie, “Okafor’s Law” was stopped following a court injunction. March 27, 2017 In "Entertainment" No doubt, movie premieres are big occasions. Big occasions that come with glamour and glitz. From the red carpet to the movie viewing, with celebrities adorning the scene like flowers would adorn a garden, it is an occasion strictly for the glossy columns. For Nollywood and anywhere else for that… March 7, 2015 In "Entertainment"